Politically-Influenced Euro Won’t Survive, Rogers Tells Boersen

-- B y   N i c h o l a s   C o m f o r t
-- 
2011-09-22T06:40:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/politically-influenced-euro-won-t-survive-rogers-tells-boersen.html
The euro is unlikely to survive
debt and economic crises and may not exist in 10 years because
it is increasingly being influenced by politicians, investor  Jim Rogers  said in an interview with Germany’s Boersen-Zeitung.  The euro offers much-needed competition to the U.S. dollar,
which may need to be replaced as a global  reserve currency  in 20
years, Boersen-Zeitung cited the chairman of Rogers Holdings as
saying.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nicholas Comfort at 
 ncomfort1@bloomberg.net  